      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">How much protein can you absorb in one meal?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Your body absorbs nearly all of the protein you eat — absorption is not the limiting factor. The real question is how much protein your muscles can actually use for repair and growth in one sitting. Research suggests 30–40g per meal is the effective dose for triggering muscle protein synthesis in men over 40, with the higher end of that range recommended due to anabolic resistance.</div>
