      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is the "30g protein absorption limit" a myth?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — the idea that you can only absorb 30g of protein per meal is a myth. Your intestines absorb amino acids continuously and can process far more than 30g. The 30g figure refers to the approximate threshold for maximally stimulating muscle protein synthesis — not an absorption ceiling. Eating 60g at one meal isn't wasted; it's absorbed and used for other bodily functions beyond muscle building.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Does protein digestion speed matter after 40?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — digestion speed affects how quickly amino acids reach the bloodstream and trigger muscle protein synthesis. Whey protein digests quickly, making it effective post-workout. Casein digests slowly over 5–7 hours. For men over 40, having a fast-digesting source earlier and a slow-digesting source before bed can optimize muscle maintenance across a full 24-hour period.</div>
