      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What happens to protein your body doesn't use for muscle?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Protein above the muscle-building threshold is used for other functions — enzymes, hormones, immune function, skin, hair, connective tissue — or broken down for energy. It is not wasted in the sense of passing through unused. It is absorbed and redirected. This is why spreading protein across meals is about optimizing muscle stimulus, not avoiding waste.</div>
